Hi Nitin,

Usually:

                        /*
                         * 1) Last transfer descriptor makes the
                         * transfer done
                         */
                        if (((void *)td) == xfer->td_transfer_last) {
                                DPRINTF("TD is last\n");
                                xhci_generic_done(xfer);
                                break;
                        }


Will be hit before xfer->td_transfer_cache hits NULL.

Could you:

print /x *xfer

For the failing USB transfer. It would be interesting to see the state.

Skipping NULL td_transfer_cache might work, but really indicates a bug somewhere else.

--HPS
